The paper discusses web annotation and the prevalence of orphaned annotations, which are annotations that can no longer be attached to their live web pages. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), web technologies (cs.WEB), natural language processing (cs.CL), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). However, given the focus on web annotation and archiving, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.WEB, cs.CL, and cs.HC.
